The compiler path confirmed that some bugs are not isolated helpers: the public bundler examples pass relative module paths, cache reads happen before any compile/config fingerprinting, and the solc wrapper can fall back to the bundled compiler. I’m doing one pass over the remaining `whatsabi` package and then I’ll write the review file.
